  "prompt": "When and how did WWI start and end?",
  "response": "World War I (WWI) began on July 28, 1914, when Austria-Hungary declared war on Serbia following the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand in Sarajevo. Due to a complex system of alliances, other European powers quickly became involved:\n\nStart:\n- Germany supported Austria-Hungary\n- Russia supported Serbia\n- France and Britain joined the Allied Powers against Germany and Austria-Hungary\n- The conflict gradually expanded into a global war\n\nEnd:\n- The war ended on November 11, 1918, with the signing of the Armistice of Compi\u00e8gne\n- Germany and the Central Powers surrendered\n- The fighting officially stopped at 11:00 AM on November 11, 1918 (now commemorated as Armistice Day/Veterans Day)\n\nKey aftermath:\n- Treaty of Versailles formally ended the war in 1919\n- Significant territorial changes in Europe\n- Collapse of four major empires (German, Austro-Hungarian, Ottoman, and Russian)\n- Approximately 20 million military and civilian deaths\n- Laid groundwork for World War II\n\nThe war lasted about 4 years and 3 months and fundamentally changed the geopolitical landscape of the world.",
